409
00:41:28,895 --> 00:41:30,215
Just don’t show your inside feeling too much.

410
00:41:30,895 --> 00:41:31,931
I don’t think I can control that.

411
00:41:33,695 --> 00:41:34,647
Then don’t make eye contact.

412
00:41:37,228 --> 00:41:42,147
Don’t let your partner know what you are thinking or feeling.

413
00:41:42,147 --> 00:41:43,680
And don’t say anything tacky.

414
00:41:45,585 --> 00:41:48,052
“Oh, it’s really good. It feels so good.”

415
00:41:48,052 --> 00:41:49,423
Damn it, Gong!

416
00:41:54,343 --> 00:41:54,885
Hey.

417
00:41:55,953 --> 00:41:57,166
Then what do you think?

418
00:41:58,336 --> 00:42:01,248
As you are doing it, don’t you think that your partner may find it weird?

419
00:42:02,298 --> 00:42:04,743
Put on some act. No need to show that you are into it.

420
00:42:05,237 --> 00:42:08,038
Just nail and bail. Then part ways.

421
00:42:08,038 --> 00:42:09,498
It's a win-win situation.

422
00:42:10,936 --> 00:42:11,882
Let me tell you this.

423
00:42:12,638 --> 00:42:14,493
This kind of sex is not love.

424
00:42:15,234 --> 00:42:16,454
It's pure sex.

425
00:42:17,767 --> 00:42:22,485
If you give too much feeling or if one of you likes it and develops a bond,

426
00:42:23,147 --> 00:42:24,480
that will be complicated.

427
00:42:35,665 --> 00:42:36,455
Gong.

428
00:42:37,879 --> 00:42:38,911
Let’s go eat Chicken Rice.

429
00:42:40,268 --> 00:42:41,486
What’s with you?

430
00:42:41,486 --> 00:42:43,202
We just talked about sex.

431
00:42:43,202 --> 00:42:45,048
How could you invite me out to eat?

432
00:42:45,469 --> 00:42:46,567
No, I don’t want to eat it.

433
00:42:47,079 --> 00:42:48,426
Didn’t you just have it yesterday?

434
00:42:50,735 --> 00:42:53,024
You look sus. There must be something.

435
00:44:57,770 --> 00:44:59,770
[Mr. Wongsakorn Thunapakarn]

436
00:45:46,749 --> 00:45:48,749
[Mrs. Jintana]

437
00:46:02,618 --> 00:46:05,962
When he brought Chicken Rice here yesterday,

438
00:46:05,962 --> 00:46:07,521
He played with a bottle of liquor.

439
00:46:07,521 --> 00:46:10,205
He was startled when my son appeared and dropped it on the floor.

440
00:46:10,205 --> 00:46:12,246
Then he ran back home.

441
00:46:12,246 --> 00:46:14,451
I didn’t do that, Uncle Jim.

442
00:46:14,451 --> 00:46:15,721
We weren’t home.

443
00:46:15,721 --> 00:46:17,455
The liquor couldn’t drop itself.

444
00:46:17,455 --> 00:46:19,454
It wasn’t me.

445
00:46:22,282 --> 00:46:24,282
It was him.

446
00:46:24,943 --> 00:46:26,992
Hey. How could you put the blame on my son?

447
00:46:28,802 --> 00:46:30,802
I said I didn’t do it.

448
00:46:30,802 --> 00:46:33,847
Your son was startled when he saw me and dropped the bottle.

449
00:46:36,368 --> 00:46:39,856
That bottle was always there. Why would he want to grab it?

450
00:46:40,479 --> 00:46:42,419
And on the day that you came?

451
00:46:42,767 --> 00:46:44,580
Why don’t you hear it from him?

452
00:46:50,173 --> 00:46:52,173
He’s already told us everything.

453
00:46:56,352 --> 00:46:58,352
You dropped it.

454
00:46:59,727 --> 00:47:02,015
Tell them you tried to drink that liquor when they weren’t around.

455
00:47:02,423 --> 00:47:04,908
- He said here he didn’t do it.
- It wasn’t me.

456
00:47:04,908 --> 00:47:06,292
He told me he didn’t.

457
00:47:06,292 --> 00:47:07,941
You friggin’ did it.

458
00:47:08,413 --> 00:47:09,647
Stop.

459
00:47:11,143 --> 00:47:13,143
You use your deafness to get you off the hook, right?

460
00:47:13,143 --> 00:47:14,537
Don’t talk to my son like that.

461
00:47:14,537 --> 00:47:16,146
But I didn’t do it.

462
00:47:16,146 --> 00:47:17,420
Li Ming, stop!

463
00:47:18,604 --> 00:47:22,145
Please excuse us for a moment.

464
00:47:22,145 --> 00:47:23,460
Get up.

465
00:47:33,394 --> 00:47:35,394
Tell me everything.

466
00:47:35,394 --> 00:47:37,715
I already told everything.

467
00:47:37,715 --> 00:47:39,848
He was sneakily drinking his father's liquor.

468
00:47:39,848 --> 00:47:43,359
When he saw me, he was startled and dropped the bottle.

469
00:47:44,159 --> 00:47:46,962
So I placed the food on the counter and left.

470
00:47:47,202 --> 00:47:48,859
That's all there is to it.

471
00:47:50,667 --> 00:47:52,667
You should have told me about it first.

472
00:47:53,677 --> 00:47:55,398
What would I do that for?

473
00:47:55,398 --> 00:47:57,922
I did nothing wrong.

474
00:48:06,292 --> 00:48:09,156
