477
00:48:24,046 --> 00:48:26,522
If we keep arguing with them like that, it will never end.

478
00:48:26,858 --> 00:48:29,025
What evidence do you want?

479
00:48:29,025 --> 00:48:31,989
I said I did nothing wrong.

480
00:48:38,269 --> 00:48:41,061
I know. But if Officer Supoch refuses to drop the matter,

481
00:48:41,061 --> 00:48:42,632
you cannot win against him.

482
00:48:48,473 --> 00:48:50,473
Can you think of this incident as bad luck?

483
00:48:51,217 --> 00:48:53,253
What bad luck?

484
00:48:53,253 --> 00:48:55,075
I don’t get it.

485
00:48:55,323 --> 00:48:57,619
I did nothing wrong.

486
00:48:59,432 --> 00:49:01,057
Because we are poor?

487
00:49:01,729 --> 00:49:03,913
They can do anything at all to us?

488
00:49:07,722 --> 00:49:09,554
I don’t want to settle it at the police station.

489
00:49:10,130 --> 00:49:12,262
What exactly do you fear?

490
00:49:12,262 --> 00:49:14,400
Because he’s a police officer?

491
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:16,850
So he has the power to do anything to us.

492
00:49:36,851 --> 00:49:38,851
To be honest, I don’t want to put you in this position.

493
00:49:38,851 --> 00:49:41,081
But this was one of his old liquor collections.

494
00:49:41,081 --> 00:49:43,943
It is worth over 10,000 baht.

495
00:49:45,959 --> 00:49:47,959
We don’t want you to think that we are mean.

496
00:49:49,727 --> 00:49:50,863
What do you think?

497
00:49:50,863 --> 00:49:52,576
Since we cannot find evidence.

498
00:49:52,576 --> 00:49:55,422
Say we split the responsibility 50/50.

499
00:49:55,422 --> 00:49:57,326
7000 baht, are you able to pay that?

500
00:50:05,382 --> 00:50:07,382
I will get money from Mrs. Hong’s money pool at the end of this month.

501
00:50:07,382 --> 00:50:09,570
I’ll pay you then.

502
00:50:09,570 --> 00:50:11,395
You don’t need to do that.

503
00:50:12,067 --> 00:50:14,067
I’ll pay you myself.

504
00:50:15,508 --> 00:50:18,659
I let you pay us in installments.

505
00:50:19,911 --> 00:50:21,911
Can I work for you instead?

506
00:50:42,683 --> 00:50:44,683
[We’re hiring daily waitstaff.]

507
00:51:07,033 --> 00:51:09,033
We have no Chicken Rice left.

508
00:51:13,623 --> 00:51:15,623
This has an owner.

509
00:51:15,839 --> 00:51:17,796
I’m not here to eat.

510
00:51:18,244 --> 00:51:22,083
I want a can of beer. Can I have that?

511
00:51:49,319 --> 00:51:51,319
Where’s everyone?

512
00:51:51,775 --> 00:51:54,168
They have gone home.

513
00:51:55,699 --> 00:51:58,827
You are the most chill Chicken Rice seller I know.

514
00:52:00,796 --> 00:52:02,796
You only saw me when I’m chilling.

515
00:52:04,149 --> 00:52:07,721
I'm a different man when my diner is packed with customers.

516
00:52:08,250 --> 00:52:11,407
What kind of person is that man?

517
00:52:13,534 --> 00:52:15,534
Just an ordinary seller

518
00:52:15,534 --> 00:52:18,751
